description:
Responsibilities:

To support Product & Marketing Manager and work as a team to execute product plans and strategy with the ultimate objective of raising brand awareness, brand building and increasing sales;
To identify a continuous stream of commercially valuable new products;
Drive product development, packaging and manage market analysis;
Product forecasting and inventory control and management;
Work closely with internal and external production / QC teams to ensure accurate execution of product development with the right quality and time;
Support ad hoc projects when required.

Requirements:

  Degree in marketing, business management, nutrition or food science background is preferable;
  Minimum 3 years product experience in retail / FMCG (bottled drinks preferred);
  Solid experience in product marketing is advantageous;
  Good communications skill in Cantonese, Mandarin and English
  Able to independently manage project and drive progress.
  Candidate with more experience will be considered as "Senior Product Marketing Officer"



We offer 5-day-work week with competitive remuneration and benefit packages to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your application letter, resume, expected salary (quoting Employer Ref:) and availability to HR Department at Hung Fook Tong, 8/F, Chuan Kei Factory Building, Nos. 15-23 Kin Hon Street, Kwai Chung, NT., H.K. or e-mail or browse our website: www.hungfooktong.com

Personal Information Collection Statement-Applicants’ personal information will be used for the recruitment and employment matters only; information will be kept in strict confidence; information of unsuccessful applicants will be shredded after recruitment process; subject to provisions under the Personal Data (Privacy) Ordinance, applicants have right to access and make corrections of their personal data

We are a US Toys Company located in TST East.  We are looking for a high caliber individual to fill in the following position:

Project Engineer - Toys

Job Specification:

Follow up orders from initial product development to bulk production;
Communicate with US head office and designers;
Liaise with vendors and internal departments for factory quotes and order commitments;
Ensure good documentation and smooth transferring projects from engineering to manufacturing.
Any ad-hoc job tasks and projects as assigned.

 Job Requirements:

Diploma or Degree holder in related engineering discipline is preferred;
Minimum 5 years related working experiences in Toys field;
Computer literacy with ERP experience;
Good command of written and spoken English, able to speak Mandarin;
Proactive, good communication skills with suppliers and inter-departments;
Immediate available is preferred.

We offer 5-day work week, medical, dental benefit and year end double paid.

Job Responsibilities: 

Serve as key technical interface with customer during the entire product life cycle from quotation, project transfer, NPI and mass production;
Serve as the technical coordinator for internal engineering departments including component, SMT, manufacturing, industrial, quality engineering and R&D;
Take lead to resolve technical issues and perform failure analysis during NPI and at Mass Production;
Support Project Manager to communicate technically with customers and internally with team members;
Prepare, approve and maintain engineering documents, including BOM, ECN, DN, QPL, part drawing, first article evaluation report, etc.;
Support Purchasing Department and Quality Assurance Team for supplier selection;
Support Purchasing Department to source the alternative materials;
Provide training and support to the team members.

Qualification:

Bachelor’s degree in Electronics Engineering;
Minimum 10 years engineering management experience with circuit design knowledge in Industrial, Automotive, Telecommunication and/or RF Wireless; products;
Capable to handle Failure Analysis;
Strong communication skills in both verbal and written English;
Station in Shenzhen plant is required.

Interested candidates, please contact us at 65368175 for company details before applying.

Responsibilities:

Maintain overall aspects of designs and engineering phase, while keeping the product development costs and timelines to market in focus;
Collaborate with cross-functioning team including the US office, design team, project team, suppliers, to ensure multiple projects are being executed according to plan or timeline;
Product Sourcing and cost analysis;
Coordinate, monitor the product design and project implementation;
Responsible for product testing, packing design and package artwork handling.

 Qualification & Requirements:

Degree or above;
2-year experiences in Children toys/Pet Products/Plastic items;
Fresh graduate will be considered;
Strong PC skills and familiar with Project handling;
Knowledge of manufacturing processes and molding processes will be an advantage;
Self-motivated, able to work under pressure, good problem-solving skills;
Good interpersonal & communication skills;
Proficient in spoken & written English and Mandarin;
Occasionally travel to overseas and China;

Responsibilities:

Lead activities in fabric/sample development, costing package coordination, preliminary screening and order tracking;
Work with vendors to establish costing plans and follow-up on fit/lab dip approval status and ensure vendors meet the product development timeline, price, and bulk quality standards;
Proficiency on doing the costing analysis and evaluate the cost breakdown correctly;
With solid experience to deal with offshore vendors and proactively to communicate with them for all sampling development & production follow up;
Is accountable to follow up on all details on production to achieve on-time delivery targets;
Proactive in price negotiation and sourcing of suppliers to meet requirements;
Deal with production issues in efficient & proactive manner and having problem solving skillset;
Perform any ad-hoc tasks/projects as assigned by the superior.

 Qualifications:

Diploma or Degree in Merchandising or textile-related discipline is an advantage;
At least 5 years relevant experience in a merchandising and/or sourcing environment, exposure with sportswear is highly preferred;
Experience in dealing with off-shore factories;
Knowledge of the U.S. retail market is an advantage;
Proficient in MS office;
Good communication, analytical and problem solving skills;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese, Mandarin preferred;
Willingness to Travel.

Interested parties, please click the 'APPLY NOW' button for application. All information received will be used for recruitment purposes only.

Requirements:
Bachelor Degree in Engineering - Mechanical / Electronic / Production; other fields also considered with strong related experience;
Minimum 8 years experience in managing OEM product design and development, preferably in both Plush toys and Hard toys;
Familiar with EU Toys Safety Regulation is a must;
Experience in featured mechanism / motorized plush toys is definitely an advantage;
Strong project management skill, strong analytical mind on problem solving;
Good command of written and spoken English is a must.         
Candidates without Toys Engineering experience will NOT be considered.
 Job Duties:

Communicate with UK R&D colleagues on a daily basis on new product development;
New product concept evaluation, feasibility studies;
Product Costing analysis;
Development from conceptual stage through to production with OEM manufacturers;
Occasional travel to China
Interested parties, please send full resume with expected salary, present salary and available date by clicking "Apply Now" or email to " hr.hk @ thecharacter.com " for interview.
(Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.)

Job Duties:

Participate in a team for MDx product development and advancement;
Responsible for planning, organizing and overseeing process or production trial and scale up, generating ideas for new products and researching feasibility in terms of profitability, resource availability and compliance with regulations;
Recording and analyzing data, investigating and testing new equipment, technology transfer, documentation and filing;
Provide technical support to cross-functional team for product quality control, validation and evaluation;
Liaise with engineering, research, technical and/or production staff, vendors, academic researchers and external collaborators to coordinate research or commercialization projects;
Responsible for writing and reading technical papers, reports, reviews and specifications, patent and grant applications; and
Report findings and project update at group and departmental meetings.

 Requirements:

MPhil/Ph.D./Postdoc in Molecular Biology, Microbiology, Biomedical Engineering, or relevant disciplines;
Proficient and meticulous in Molecular techniques are preferable;
Hands-on experience in clinical research/ healthcare product, medical device or Point-Of-Care systems development, CE, FDA, or China NMPA application, ISO 9001 and ISO13485 process management will be beneficial;
Strong team spirit, interpersonal and communication skills, good English writing and reading ability; and
Proactive, creative, positive attitude, result-oriented, capable of multi-tasking along with problem-solving expertise and capable of independent in-depth research.

If you are passionate, driven and looking for a new and exciting opportunity within a successful and growing company, this may be the right role for you.

Please click “Apply Now” to submit your application.

For more info, please visit our web page at http://www.diagcorlifescience.com/


We will only consider applicants who apply directly to our firm and not through recruitment agencies. All applications will be treated in strict confidence. Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only. Applicants who do not hear from us within 4 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful and the applications will be destroyed within 6 months.

Responsibilities:

Review current production process flow and liaise continuous improvement activities with cross-functional parties;
Formulate and maintain standard time of each production process;
Conduct Time and Motion Study on production processes;
Monitor and enhance productivity of production lines and other related process;
Coordinate Lean projects such as 5S, TPM etc. as required;
Assist Production Training and maintain workers capability records;
Handle ad hoc projects or other duties as assigned.

Requirements:

Degree holder in industrial engineering, manufacturing engineering or related disciplines;
4 years or above working experience in Industrial Engineering or Food industry sector;
Sound experience in Pre-determined Motion Time System is an advantage;
Work independently and prioritize work on hand;
Good leadership, inter-personal skills and pro-active team player;
Strong analytical thinking and problem solving skills;
Proficiency in MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint and English & Chinese word processing;
Good command in written and spoken English and Cantonese;
Immediate available is highly preferred.

Staff Benefits

5-day work week
Birthday& Wedding Leave
Free Meal & Shuttle Bus
Staff Purchase Benefits
Medical Insurance Coverage

All applications and data collected will be treated in strict confidence and used exclusively for recruitment purposes.  Only short listed candidates will be invited for interview.  The company will retain the applications for a maximum period of 6 months and may refer suitable candidates to other vacancies within the Group.

Assist Quality Control Manager in various QC assignments including understanding of clients’ product protocols, quality procedures, lab-tests and production schedule along with factory audits;
Quality control knowledge and experience in consumable items, particularly Ceramic Table Top, Cutlery/Kitchenware, Beach products, Umbrella, Natural Fiber Storage is preferred;
Be able to read client manuals outline, summarize important points for QA/QC/Merchandising and co-ordination with factories;
Good organization and project management skills;
Good command of written and spoken English / Chinese / Mandarin;
Diploma or Degree Holder preferred;
Working experience: minimum 1-2 years.



Interested parties, please send your resume, expected salary & the earliest available date by clicking “APPLY NOW”.

Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.
